n visual appeal and readability. My goal is for the app to remain visually and functionally good as the user interface adapts, particularly as the `Visualizer.tsx` changes. I will also make sure the analysis sections will respond appropriately.\n\n\n**Refining Text Presentation**\n\nI\'m now refining text presentation in `App.tsx` for enhanced readability across devices. I\'m focusing on adjusting font sizes and spacing using Tailwind\'s responsive classes. I\'ve updated the `currentLog` text display, using `text-2xl sm:text-4xl` and `leading-snug` to create a more adaptable presentation. I\'m also addressing the \"\354\210\230\354\213\240 \354\244\221\" status and time display for consistency. My aim is to make the text scale smoothly and maintain clarity on all screen sizes, especially on smaller devices.\n\n\n**Enhancing Visual Feedback**\n\nI\'m currently revising the user feedback display in `App.tsx`. I\'m refining the \"\353\247\220\354\224\200\355\225\230\354\213\234\353\212\224 \354\244\221...\", \"\353\266\204\354\204\235 \354\244\221...\", and \"\352\260\220\354\247\200\353\220\234 \354\226\270\354\226\264\" text presentations. I\'m focusing on consistent visual hierarchy using Tailwind classes for size, weight, and spacing. I\'m also ensuring the loader\'s size and the overall layout are responsive to maintain clarity.\n\n\n**Refining Introductory Elements**\n\nI\'m now revising the introductory display in `App.tsx`. I\'m focusing on the \"Start\" message and visual elements. My goals are responsive design, font resizing, and consistent spacing across all devices. I\'m adjusting text size and spacing to improve user experience. My target is an engaging and clear user introduction.\n\n\n**Adjusting Button & Visualizer**\n\nI am now adjusting the button style in `App.tsx`, and I\'m updating the `Visualizer.tsx` component to reduce its size on smaller screens. I\'m focusing on ensuring responsiveness, and aiming for an improved user experience across all devices.\n\n\n**Refining Status Display**\n\nI\'m now refining the status display within `App.tsx` and verifying the MIME type fallback for iOS compatibility. I\'ve integrated `getSupportedMimeType` to ensure audio recording compatibility. My next step is making certain the \'STANDBY\' and \'ACTIVE\' display dynamically and clearly with CSS classes. I\'m also ensuring the canvas size and positioning work well on smaller screens.\n\n\n"
