  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I have built the complete data analysis and model training pipeline for the AccentLens MVP. The system focuses on analyzing *how* the user pronounces English by extracting acoustic features, completely skipping speech-to-text.\n\nHere is a summary of the implementation:\n\n- **Dataset Inspection (`analyze_dataset.py`)**: Automatically scans the `dataset/` directory to count files, average audio durations, and checks for class imbalances.\n- **Audio Preprocessing (`audio_utils.py`)**: Safely loads audio, converts it to 16kHz mono, trims leading/trailing silence, and normalizes the volume, while rejecting files that are too short.\n- **Feature Extraction (`feature_extractor.py`)**: Extracts MFCCs, then computes the mean, standard deviation, deltas, and delta-deltas across time to create a robust, fixed-length acoustic feature vector. Includes a placeholder for Wav2Vec2/HuBERT embeddings.\n- **Model Training & Evaluation (`train_model.py`)**: Trains a `RandomForestClassifier` on the extracted features. It saves the model, label encoder, and extensive metadata to the `models/` directory. It also generates an evaluation report and a confusion matrix heat map in the `reports/` folder.\n- **Prediction (`predict.py`)**: Processes new audio through the same pipeline and outputs probability scores for each accent group.\n- **Privacy-Aware Post-Learning (`post_learning.py`)**: Allows users to confirm or correct the predicted accent. If they consent, the system saves only the extracted feature vectors to `feedback/confirmed_features.csv` (never the raw voice files) so you can retrain the model later.\n- **Streamlit Interface (`app.py`)**: Created an interactive web app with tabs for Dataset Analysis, Model Training, Accent Prediction, Post-Learning Feedback, and an About page that clearly explains the methodology and ethical boundaries (i.e. we do not predict nationality).\n\n### How to use it locally\n\n1. Put your audio dataset into the `dataset/` folder. Each subfolder should be named after the accent (e.g., `dataset/Korean-accented English/`, `dataset/American English/`).\n2. Run `pip install -r requirements.txt`.\n3. Start the UI by running `streamlit run app.py`."
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
